  3. Lineup page instructs me to tap players that don't exist.
  I go to Lineup. Instruction banner says "Tap a player to select them, then tap where to move them." Every slot says "Empty." The bench says "Empty." There are zero players. The instruction references an action I literally cannot perform on this page in this state. It should say "Draft players to fill your lineup" with a link to the
  draft room or admin panel.

  **How to fix (UX-018):** In `app/team/[teamId]/lineup/LineupManager.tsx` (or its parent page), add a pre-draft state check: if the roster is empty (zero `RosterEntry` rows), replace the instruction banner with a pre-draft-specific message: "Your roster is empty. Draft players first, then come back to set your lineup." Include a link to the league overview or draft room. The click-to-swap instruction banner should only appear when there is at least one player on the roster. This is a P0 — it actively misleads users about what actions are available.

  **Covered by:** UX-018 (net-new)

