  4. 447 Free Agents, but can I pick them up?
  On the Roster page, Free Agents tab shows 447 players. Each has an "Add" button. I click Add — does this bypass the draft? Is this a waiver claim? The page doesn't explain that these players are available after the draft and waiver process. A pre-draft user clicking "Add" on a free agent is either going to do something unexpected
  or get an error with no explanation.

  **How to fix (UX-019):** In `app/team/[teamId]/roster/RosterManager.tsx`, add a contextual banner or inline note on the Free Agents tab that explains the add/waiver process based on league state. Pre-draft: show a banner "Free agent adds open after the draft. Players are added by waiver claim during the season." Post-draft / in-season: show "Players dropped within 48 hours are on waivers. Others are immediate adds." This requires reading `league.status` (already available as a prop) to choose the appropriate copy. No schema changes needed.

  **Covered by:** UX-019 (net-new)

