  6. The announcements box gates the league overview before setup is done.
  First thing I see on the league overview as commissioner: a large textarea prompt to post an announcement. I haven't set up my draft. I haven't invited my managers. But the app is asking me to communicate to a league that doesn't have anyone in it yet. The commissioner action strip ("Draft setup needed → Take action") is below this box, visually secondary to it. The announcement box shouldn't appear until all teams have joined the league and it likely doesn't need this much real estate, regardless.

  **How to fix:** Already captured. Move `AnnouncementForm` below the playoff race table and matchup sections in `app/league/[leagueId]/page.tsx`. Consider hiding it entirely when `league.status === "PRE_DRAFT"` and fewer than `league.maxTeams` have joined — there is no one to announce to yet. File: `app/league/[leagueId]/page.tsx`.

  **Covered by:** UX-008 (already in Sprint 10). The additional "hide it pre-draft when no one has joined yet" nuance is worth noting in UX-008's acceptance criteria but does not require a new story.

