  10. The dashboard skeleton shows a logged-out nav.
  After logging in, during the ~2 second load, the top nav still shows "Login." I briefly wonder if my login worked. The nav should resolve auth state before rendering (or at least show a loading spinner in place of "Login" rather than the unauthenticated link).

  **How to fix (UX-021):** In `app/layout.tsx`, the top nav auth section renders `<a href="/login">Login</a>` when the user session is not yet resolved. During the server-side rendering gap (Next.js hydration window), the client briefly sees the unauthenticated state. Fix options: (a) On the client, replace the "Login" link with a neutral loading indicator (`•••` or a skeleton chip) until the client hydration confirms auth status. (b) Use Next.js `headers()` / cookie-based server component rendering to ensure the auth state is always resolved server-side before HTML is sent. Option (b) is preferred if the nav is already a server component — confirm whether `app/layout.tsx` reads `pwhl_user_email` synchronously. File: `app/layout.tsx`.

  **Covered by:** UX-021 (net-new)

