  11. "Season" tab (team) and "Schedule" tab (league) are the same word but mean different things.
  The league nav has "Schedule" = fantasy matchup schedule. The team nav has "Season" = also shows a schedule (PWHL game schedule for my players). A user clicking between league-level and team-level nav is likely to conflate these two tabs or explore the wrong one first.

  **How to fix (UX-022):** Rename the team-nav "Season" tab to "Record" (which is already in BF-007) or "My Season." Separately, confirm the league nav's "Schedule" tab is clearly labeled as fantasy matchup schedule (not PWHL game schedule). The rename in BF-007 (Performance → Record) and the UX-006 league nav alignment work together to reduce this confusion. Once BF-007 ships ("Record") and UX-006 ships (unified nav visual language), the distinction will be clearer. No additional rename needed beyond what BF-007 specifies — the ambiguity comes from similar-sounding names, not identical ones.

  **Covered by:** BF-007 (already in Sprint 10 — renaming "Performance" to "Record" directly addresses the naming ambiguity). UX-006 (Sprint 11 — league nav unification improves visual distinction between nav zones). No separate story needed.

