  12. Analysis tab is visible but always empty pre-season.
  Seven team nav tabs are exposed to a pre-draft user. Five of them show empty states or nothing useful. "Analysis" specifically says "Not enough scored weeks yet — check
  back after week 2." There's no preview of what analysis will show — no wireframe preview, no description. It's just a dead end with no incentive to return. Either hide
  this tab pre-season, or describe what it will show: "See week-by-week FP trends, consistency scores, and schedule difficulty — available after Week 2."

  **How to fix:** The Analysis page empty state should describe what the tab will show and when it will activate. Use `EmptyState.tsx` with copy: "Analysis unlocks after Week 2. You'll see week-by-week FP trends, your strongest position groups, and free agent upgrade recommendations." File: `app/team/[teamId]/analysis/page.tsx`.

  **Covered by:** UX-016 (which specifically lists `app/team/[teamId]/analysis/page.tsx` as one of the four pages needing a page-specific empty state message). The "hide the tab pre-season" variant is a deeper scope change not captured by UX-016 — if we want to pursue tab hiding, that warrants a Design Backlog entry.

